cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper deals with porting code from one architecture (CPU) to another (GPU) and predicting the potential speed-up. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes a framework that relies solely on program properties collected using static analysis of the CPU source code. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper addresses the problem of porting code from one architecture to another, which is a common software engineering problem. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses machine learning in a supervised setting to predict the potential speed-up of porting code from CPU to GPU. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with optimizing the performance of a system (porting code from CPU to GPU) using machine learning.
